{"id": 225018466, "title": "Calgary Herald letters, May 29: Too many people, or too few?", "text": "John Bates, Calgary Stick to facts in housing debate Re: Opinion: What\u2019s keeping us from helping people find a home, Opinion, May 25 The answer to John Van Sloten\u2019s question is that not everyone believes in the socialist trope of \u201csacrificing for the greater good\u201d when it comes to densification. Pointing out his own response as selfish and then slyly attributing selfishness to the majority who do not support blanket rezoning is disingenuous, but it certainly highlights his virtuous change of heart. This is more than just scooching over. The benefits of the utopian density he lists may carry some truth but then there\u2019s reality. This reality is being lived right now by many and it does not measure up to the Mr. Rogers\u2019 neighbourhood he glowingly describes. How does he suggest their misery be dealt with? Hundreds of intelligent, caring, innovative citizens gave their oral and written submissions. They had valid concerns, logical arguments and reasonable solutions. It fell on deaf ears, hard hearts and prideful minds. As was reiterated by so many, minds had already been made up. Where was the \u201cgreater good\u201d here? No one is arguing that others do not need housing, but this issue needs to be thoughtfully resolved using reality and facts, and not just warm fuzzy feelings. Pathological altruism and virtue do not always lend themselves to optimum outcomes. Gail Singh, Calgary", "summary": "I\u2019m just a simpleton who doesn\u2019t understand immigration and population growth in Canada. Someone explain this to me like I\u2019m five. I keep hearing that Canada has too many people. Schools are overloaded and class sizes getting bigger. No slots are available in child care and wait lists are sometimes three years. There are lineups [&#8230;]", "url": "https://calgaryherald.com/opinion/letters/calgary-herald-letters-may-29-too-many-people-or-too-few", "image": "https://smartcdn.gprod.postmedia.digital/calgaryherald/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/population-growth-0116-ph.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:00:04", "author": "Calgary Herald,Michele Jarvie", "authors": ["Calgary Herald", "Michele Jarvie"], "language": "en", "source_country": "ca", "sentiment": 0.317}